    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-18T18:28:04+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-18T18:28:04+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T08:58:04Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-18T08:58:04Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A low pressure system south of the Bight will drift to the south east while a trough extends across western coasts late on Thursday. This trough will linger along the coastline into Friday, developing into the cold front that will clear into the east early Saturday. A high pressure system will begin to move in from the west on Saturday, cross the Bight, slowly drifting to eastern SA by Monday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW015" description="Mount Lofty Ranges" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-18T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely later this evening. Winds northwesterly 25 to 40 km/h decreasing to 25 to 30 km/h in the late evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Winds west to northwesterly 20 to 30 km/h turning southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning and early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 12 and 15.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog in the north. High chance of showers in the south, medium chance elsewhere. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h tending south to southeasterly early in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 11 and 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-21T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-22T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-20T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-21T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Medium chance of showers about the southern Fleurieu Peninsula, slight chance elsewhere. The chance of morning frost near the Barossa Valley. Light winds. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 11 and 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-22T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-23T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-21T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-22T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the south, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming west to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 6 with daytime temperatures reaching between 12 and 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
